claim.claim-text:
1. A method for dynamically controlling variation during an exposure step of a patterning process using an exposure tool comprising:
measuring a set of one or more pattern attributes at a set of discrete locations on a substrate, the substrate having two or more fields and at least one field having two or more of the set of discrete locations;
selecting a first set of basis functions representing a first variation of the set of one or more pattern attributes over a first set of discrete locations within a first field, and selecting a second set of basis functions representing a second variation of the set of one or more pattern attributes over a second set of discrete locations within a second field;
defining a first set of reference locations within a field;
defining a second set of reference locations over the substrate;
constructing a first orthogonal set of functions from the first set of basis functions on the first set of reference locations and constructing a second orthogonal set of functions from the second set of basis function on the second set of reference locations; and
constructing a third orthogonal set of basis functions comprised of the first set of basis functions and the second set of basis functions and the product of each of the first set of basis functions with each of the second set of basis functions;
fitting the third orthogonal set of functions to the measured set of one or more pattern attributes at the set of discrete locations;
determining, as a result of said fitting, a set of coefficients of the third orthogonal set of functions; and
minimizing a variation in the one or more pattern attributes by adjusting the exposure tool or the patterning process according to one or more said determined set of coefficients.

3. A method for controlling a nonlinear variation in a manufacturing step using a process tool comprising:
measuring one or more attributes of a product being manufactured by said process tool at a set of one or more discrete times or locations spanning one or more finite temporal or spatial domains, the product having two or more fields and at least one field having two or more of the set of discrete locations;
selecting a first set of basis functions representing a first variation in the set of one or more product attributes over a first set of discrete locations within a first field, and selecting a second set of basis functions representing a second variation of the set of one or more pattern attributes over a second set of discrete locations within a second field;
defining a set of reference times or locations distributed on the product being manufactured, said defined locations comprising a first set of reference locations within a field and a second set of reference locations over the product;
constructing a first orthogonal set of functions from the first set of basis functions, said first orthogonal set of functions being constructed from the set of basis functions on the defined first set of reference locations, and constructing a second orthogonal set of functions from the second set of basis function on the second set of reference locations;
constructing a third orthogonal set of basis functions comprised of the first set of basis functions and the second set of basis functions and the product of each of the first set of basis functions with each of the second set of basis functions;
fitting the third orthogonal set of functions to the measured set of one or more product attributes at the set of discrete times or locations;
determining, as a result of said fitting, a set of coefficients of the third orthogonal set of functions; and
minimizing a variation in the one or more product attributes by adjusting the process tool corresponding to one or more of the coefficients.

7. A system for controlling nonlinear variation in a manufacturing step using a process tool comprising:
a measuring device for dynamically measuring one or more attributes of a product being manufactured at a set of one or more discrete times or locations spanning one or more finite temporal or spatial domains, the product having two or more fields and at least one field having two or more of the set of discrete locations;
a memory device;
a processing device operatively coupled to the memory device and configured to perform a method comprising:
selecting a first set of basis functions representing a first variation in the set of one or more product attributes over a first set of discrete locations within a first field, and selecting a second set of basis functions representing a second variation of the set of one or more pattern attributes over a second set of discrete locations within a second field;
defining a set of reference times or locations distributed on the product being manufactured, said defined locations comprising a first set of reference locations within a field and a second set of reference locations over the product;
constructing a first orthogonal set of the set of functions from the first set of basis functions on the defined first set of reference locations, and constructing a second orthogonal set of functions from the second set of basis function on the second set of reference locations;
constructing a third orthogonal set of basis functions comprised of the first set of basis functions and the second set of basis functions and the product of each of the first set of basis functions with each of the second set of basis functions;
fitting the third orthogonal set of functions to the measured set of one or more product attributes at the set of discrete times or locations;
determining, as a result of said fitting, a set of coefficients of the third orthogonal set of functions; and
minimizing a variation in the one or more product attributes by adjusting the process tool corresponding to one or more of the coefficients.

11. A computer program product for controlling a nonlinear variation in a manufacturing step using a process tool, the computer program device comprising a storage medium readable by a processing circuit and storing instructions run by the processing circuit for performing a method, the method comprising:
initiating a measurement, by a measurement device, of one or more attributes of a product being manufactured by said process tool at a set of one or more discrete times or locations spanning one or more finite temporal or spatial domains, the product having two or more fields and at least one field having two or more of the set of discrete locations;
selecting a first set of basis functions representing a first variation in the set of one or more product attributes over a first set of discrete locations within a first field, and selecting a second set of basis functions representing a second variation of the set of one or more pattern attributes over a second set of discrete locations within a second field;
defining a set of reference times or locations distributed on the product being manufactured, said defined locations comprising a first set of reference locations within a field and a second set of reference locations over the product;
constructing a first orthogonal set of functions from the first set of basis functions on the defined first set of reference locations, and constructing a second orthogonal set of functions from the second set of basis function on the second set of reference locations;
constructing a third orthogonal set of basis functions comprised of the first set of basis functions and the second set of basis functions and the product of each of the first set of basis functions with each of the second set of basis functions;
fitting the third orthogonal set of functions to the measured set of one or more product attributes at the set of discrete times or locations;
determining, as a result of said fitting, a set of coefficients of the third orthogonal set of functions; and
minimizing a variation in the one or more product attributes by adjusting the process tool corresponding to one or more of the coefficients.
